fields.caption: Order Management
fields.extract: Making the leap from paper based order management to a process managed entirely on Outlook
fields.story:
Our client still had an entirely paper based process for order management. The process was:
Orders received as email
printed out, email moved to year/month folder
sorted by region
placed in trays
collected by order entry clerk
order entered
paper copy stamped and order number noted
paper copy filed per customer

Sub AddlinesToSummary()

' Insert Additional line to the Summary Sheet - for additional detail cost sheets
' Created 25/5/09 by D Thierry
' ShortCut = Ctlr+L
' this macro inserts a blank line into the summary sheet above the currently active line
' it then copied the formulas from the previous line to the nex line

    Rows(ActiveCell.Row).Insert Shift:=xlDown, CopyOrigin:=xlFormatFromLeftOrAbove
    tablewidth = Cells(4, Columns.Count).End(xlToLeft).Column
    newrow = ActiveCell.Row
    copyrow = newrow - 1
    'uses row 4 as the totals row to determine width of the formulas to copy
    Range("A" & copyrow).Resize(1, tablewidth).Copy Destination:=Range("A" & newrow).Resize(1, tablewidth)
    Cells(newrow, 1).Value = ""
    
End Sub

Function GetWorksheetFromCodeName(wb As Workbook, CodeName As String) As Worksheet
    Dim ws As Worksheet
    For Each ws In wb.Worksheets
        Debug.Print ws.Name, ws.CodeName
        If StrComp(ws.CodeName, CodeName, vbTextCompare) = 0 Then
            Set GetWorksheetFromCodeName = ws
            Exit Function
        End If
    Next ws
End Function

Function RowsInBlock(sh As String, startRow As Long, col1 As Long, col2 As Long) As Long
'startRow - is the starting point to test from 
'col1 and col2 used as boundaries for the test

Dim ws As Worksheet, maxR As Long, col As Long, lr As Long
Set ws = GetWorksheetFromCodeName(ThisWorkbook, sh)

For col = col1 To col2
   lr = ws.Cells(Rows.Count, col).End(xlUp).Row
   If lr > maxR Then maxR = lr
Next col
If maxR > startRow Then RowsInBlock = maxR - startRow Else RowsInBlock = 0
End Function

Sub MakePDF(whichSh As Worksheet, DraftName As String)
' make this generic to call it for any sheet
Dim ChosenSh As Worksheet, myFile As Variant, strFile As String
On Error GoTo errHandler
Set ChosenSh = whichSh
strFile = Range("saveFolder") & "\" & DraftName & ".pdf"
myFile = Application.GetSaveAsFilename _
    (InitialFileName:=strFile, _
        FileFilter:="PDF Files (*.pdf), *.pdf", _
        Title:="Select Folder and FileName to save")
If myFile <> "False" Then
    ChosenSh.ExportAsFixedFormat _
        Type:=xlTypePDF, _
        fileName:=myFile, _
        Quality:=xlQualityStandard, _
        IncludeDocProperties:=True, _
        IgnorePrintAreas:=False, _
        OpenAfterPublish:=False
    fileName = myFile
    'MsgBox "PDF file has been created."
End If
ExitHandler:
    Exit Sub
errHandler:
    MsgBox "Could not create PDF file"
    Resume ExitHandler

End Sub

Private Function IsArrayAllocated(Arr As Variant) As Boolean
''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''
' IsArrayAllocated
' Returns True or False indicating if Arr is an allocated
' array.
''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''
    On Error Resume Next
    Dim V As Variant
    IsArrayAllocated = True
    V = Arr(LBound(Arr, 1))
    If IsError(V) = True Then
        IsArrayAllocated = False
    End If
    If (UBound(Arr, 1) < LBound(Arr, 1)) Then
        IsArrayAllocated = False
    End If
    
End Function

Function ConvTime(TimeS As String) As Single

'The function converts time entered in the format 2.17pm
'into a floating number for use in date/time calculations

Dim am As Boolean, pm As Boolean, dot As Integer, ap As Integer, pmAdd As Integer
Dim amFound As Integer, pmFound As Integer, hStr As String, mStr As String
amFound = InStr(1, TimeS, "am", vbTextCompare)
pmFound = InStr(1, TimeS, "pm", vbTextCompare)
dot = InStr(1, TimeS, ".", vbTextCompare)
If amFound > 0 Then am = True: pmAdd = 0
If pmFound > 0 Then pm = True: pmAdd = 12
On Error GoTo EH
If dot = 0 And (am = True Or pm = True) Then
    hStr = Left(TimeS, amFound + pmFound - 1)
    ConvTime = (CInt(hStr) + pmAdd) / 23
    If ConvTime >= 1 Then ConvTime = ConvTime - 1
    Exit Function
End If
If dot > 0 And (am = True Or pm = True) Then
        hStr = Left(TimeS, dot - 1)
        mStr = Mid(TimeS, dot + 1, 2)
        ConvTime = (CInt(hStr) + pmAdd + CInt(mStr) / 60) / 24
        If ConvTime >= 1 Then ConvTime = ConvTime - 1
        Exit Function
    Else
        ConvTime = 0
        Exit Function
End If

EH:
ConvTime = 0

End Function

Function CleanNumbers(Inc As String) As String
' cleans number strings of non numeric characters
' can be used to convert phone numbers or others
Dim i As Integer, temp As String, Out As String
If Len(Inc) > 1 Then
        For i = 1 To Len(Inc)
            temp = Mid(Inc, i, 1)
            If IsNumeric(temp) Then Out = Out & temp
            Debug.Print Out
        Next i
        CleanNumbers = Out
    Else
        CleanNumbers = Inc
End If

End Function

Private Sub btnSubmit_Click()
Dim output(1 To 7) As Variant, tbl As ListObject, ws As Worksheet, new_row As ListRow
If Me.txtFBVerifier <> "" Or Me.textFBVendor <> "" Then
    output(1) = Now()
    output(3) = Me.txtProvider
    output(4) = Me.txtBatch
    output(5) = Me.txtVerifier
    output(6) = Me.textFBVendor
    output(7) = Me.txtFBVerifier
    output(2) = Me.txtJob
    Set ws = Sheets("FeedbackRecords")
    Set tbl = ws.ListObjects("tbl_Output")
    Set new_row = tbl.ListRows.Add
    For i = 1 To 7
    
        new_row.Range(i) = output(i)
    Next i
    Unload Me
End If

End Sub
